08/06/2008
PATRAS, Greece -- An earthquake measuring between 6.1 and 6.5 on the Richter scale shook southwestern Greece Sunday (June 8th) at around 3:25 pm local time, according to Greek media. Authorities said buildings were damaged and local residents left their homes. There were no immediate reports of injuries.
Ileia prefecture in the Western Peloponnese is thought to be the epicentre, but residents as far away as Athens said they felt the tremor. (ERT, Athens News Agency)
